# --- Commit Message Guidelines ---
# Header: <type>(<scope>): <subject> (Max 50 chars, no period at end)
# 
# type: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore, revert
# scope: Optional. Affected area (e.g., UI, logic, db)
# subject: Short description of the change
#
# Body: Detailed description (What & Why). Wrap at 72 chars.
#
# Footer: Issues reference (e.g., Fixes #123), BREAKING CHANGE
# ---------------------------------

# [Type]
# feat:     New feature
# fix:      Bug fix
# docs:     Documentation changes
# style:    Formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change
# refactor: Refactoring code, eg. renaming variables
# perf:     Improvements for performance
# test:     Adding missing tests
# chore:    Updating grunt tasks etc; no production code change
# revert:   Revert to a previous commit
